    "created_at": "2026-06-06T15:07:54Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-06-06T15:07:54Z",
    "body": "The fix should probably treat `reasoning_content` as provider-owned replay metadata, not normal assistant text.\n\nStoring it in `AIMessage.additional_kwargs.reasoning_content` sounds right, but the reverse converter needs a narrow rule:\n\n- preserve and re-emit it only for providers/models that accept or require that field\n- keep it attached to the exact assistant message that produced the tool call\n- include a regression test where the next request sequence is assistant-with-tool_calls-and-reasoning_content, then tool result, then the follow-up model call\n\nThe exact-message attachment matters. If middleware or streaming aggregation moves the field to a later AIMessage, the request can still look superficially complete while DeepSeek rejects the replay or, worse, accepts a transcript with the wrong reasoning state bound to the wrong tool call.\n\nI would also test `reasoning.effort: \"none\"` separately, because user intent there is confusing: if the provider still returns/requires replay metadata, the client should either preserve it or make thinking truly disabled end-to-end.\n",
